The stunning great room features an open floor plan including living room, dining area, and kitchen with floor-to-ceiling windows, magnificent rock fireplace (firewood provided), beamed ceiling, wood plank floors, 60" flatscreen TV, elk antler chandelier over the dining room table, and a high end, fully-stocked kitchen with marble counters and swivel barstools. The master bedroom has a king bed, flat-screen TV, and en-suite bathroom with double vanity, jetted tub and glassed-in shower, while the guest bedroom includes a queen bed and en-suite bathroom with double vanity and walk-in shower. For extra sleeping space the living room couch folds out to a queen bed, and there is also an inflatable mattress available. There is also a powder room, laundry room, and one car garage, along with a stored high chair and Pack 'n Play for families with children. Redwood decks, complete with gas grill and patio furniture, encircle the property on three sides, ensuring lots of extra space for enjoying the great outdoors. The entire home is beautifully furnished in a tasteful western style, and stays comfortably cool in the summer and delightfully cozy in the winter (think flannel sheets and down comforters). It is charmingly landscaped with aspens, pines, and cottonwoods, along with wildflower baskets in the summer and piles of legendary powder snow in the winter. And, if you're lucky, you just may see moose, elk, buffalo and other wildlife wandering around the neighborhood or taking a nap on the lawnl
